cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method for learning a non-linear CCA projection in an end-to-end manner. It also addresses the weakness of previous CCA methods in discriminative tasks such as multi-view learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as multi-view learning is a common problem in computer vision, and the paper shows significant improvement in cross-view classification. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed method involves optimizing a task objective in addition to the CCA projection. 

It could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) as CCA is widely used for multimodal data analysis, which is a common problem in multimedia. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the proposed method involves learning a non-linear CCA projection in an end-to-end manner, which is a common approach in neural networks.
